data.chText: （房屋底层有顶半敞的）走廊，游廊
data.enText: a platform with an open front and a roof, built onto the side of a house on the ground floor

data.chText: 饭后我们坐在游廊上交谈。
data.enText: After dinner, we sat talking on the veranda.
a roof over the part of the street where people walk in front of a shop/store

means: (房屋底层有顶半敞的)走廊，游廊

tr: a porch along the outside of a building (sometimes partly enclosed)

value.def: A veranda is a roofed platform along the outside of a house.

example.ex: They had their coffee and tea on the veranda.
example.tran: 他们在阳台上喝咖啡和茶。

value.tran: （房屋外带屋顶的）走廊，游廊,阳台
